254
00:14:35,867 --> 00:14:38,661
- What's your problem?
- I don't want you to get your hopes up.

255
00:14:38,878 --> 00:14:41,162
- She's done.
- Why not give it another shot?

256
00:14:42,348 --> 00:14:43,583
What's he got to lose?

257
00:14:48,338 --> 00:14:50,362
I mean, what do I have to lose?

258
00:14:55,606 --> 00:14:58,110
Did you guys just drag me
here for lunch to torture me?

259
00:14:58,285 --> 00:15:01,501
I should be getting used to
double-beef burgers and the fryolator.

260
00:15:01,997 --> 00:15:03,961
We are not torturing you.

261
00:15:04,136 --> 00:15:05,703
We are inspiring you.

262
00:15:05,875 --> 00:15:07,443
This is your dream.

263
00:15:08,118 --> 00:15:11,061
Come on, how many times
have you done pilates

264
00:15:11,235 --> 00:15:14,070
- to the CU fight song?
- Who cares. I'm done with it forever.

265
00:15:14,477 --> 00:15:17,362
Why, because some jaded college
counselor said you won't get in here?

266
00:15:17,535 --> 00:15:19,301
Come on you are not a quitter.

267
00:15:19,545 --> 00:15:21,452
When have you ever
taken no for an answer?

268
00:15:22,296 --> 00:15:25,352
This morning, at the coffee shop.
They were out of soy.

269
00:15:25,598 --> 00:15:27,221
You should have made them get more.

270
00:15:27,398 --> 00:15:28,970
Because that's who you are.

271
00:15:29,146 --> 00:15:32,532
Remember at Hermès when they
were all sold out of the Birkin bag?

272
00:15:32,707 --> 00:15:36,132
- What'd you do?
- I called the regional manager,

273
00:15:36,305 --> 00:15:37,972
demanded they have
the salesgirl fired.

274
00:15:38,258 --> 00:15:39,122
Exactly.

275
00:15:39,257 --> 00:15:40,432
And then what happened?

276
00:15:40,698 --> 00:15:43,183
- They tracked down the bag.
- And?

277
00:15:44,678 --> 00:15:45,871
And I bought two...

278
00:15:46,045 --> 00:15:48,400
the blue calfskin,
the brown crocodile.

279
00:15:48,668 --> 00:15:50,360
Right, because you are Naomi Clark.

280
00:15:50,577 --> 00:15:53,191
When somebody says you can't
have something, you get them fired.

281
00:15:53,368 --> 00:15:55,432
Which, for the record,
I do have a problem with,

282
00:15:55,606 --> 00:15:57,710
but you don't, so it doesn't matter.

283
00:15:58,127 --> 00:16:00,701
You go after what you want
and you don't take no for an answer.

284
00:16:01,587 --> 00:16:02,732
What the...?!

285
00:16:03,107 --> 00:16:04,703
Sorry about that.

286
00:16:10,835 --> 00:16:12,002
You have a good arm.

287
00:16:17,488 --> 00:16:19,402
You're right.
You're right!

288
00:16:19,948 --> 00:16:22,172
I'm not going to let
some college counselor,

289
00:16:22,347 --> 00:16:25,211
who wears an ankle bracelet
under her stockings, get in my way.

290
00:16:25,385 --> 00:16:27,821
I just have to find a way
to get into CU.

291
00:16:27,996 --> 00:16:28,901
And I will.

292
00:16:29,155 --> 00:16:30,652
That's what we wanna hear.

293
00:16:31,995 --> 00:16:33,243
Oh, my God!

294
00:16:33,715 --> 00:16:35,190
I'm wearing sweatpants!

295
00:16:53,057 --> 00:16:54,920
The only thing that would
make me happier

296
00:16:55,096 --> 00:16:57,970
is if you had a refrigerator
right by your bed.

297
00:16:59,625 --> 00:17:01,203
With a pot roast inside.

298
00:17:02,507 --> 00:17:03,943
I'm so famished.

299
00:17:04,485 --> 00:17:06,182
But I'm thinking more like

300
00:17:06,448 --> 00:17:08,100
fried chicken and waffles.

301
00:17:11,865 --> 00:17:13,303
I forgot to tell you.

302
00:17:13,478 --> 00:17:16,433
Say you have Roscoe's in your book bag,
and all is forgiven.

303
00:17:16,607 --> 00:17:18,321
No, but it is about food.

304
00:17:19,656 --> 00:17:21,460
It's about dinner actually.

305
00:17:22,115 --> 00:17:24,492
Teddy asked us to double
date with him and some chick.

306
00:17:24,665 --> 00:17:25,660
What? No.

307
00:17:27,306 --> 00:17:29,041
I don't want to double date.

308
00:17:29,486 --> 00:17:30,291
Why not?

309
00:17:31,116 --> 00:17:32,372
Because...

310
00:17:32,777 --> 00:17:35,552
I would rather
just be with you alone.

311
00:17:35,728 --> 00:17:38,210
Me, too, but he already asked.

312
00:17:38,928 --> 00:17:40,223
So just say no.

313
00:17:40,486 --> 00:17:42,802
I already told him yes.
He wants to impress a girl.

314
00:17:43,188 --> 00:17:46,562
He asked me for a favor.
It's one night. What's the big deal?

315
00:17:50,138 --> 00:17:51,240
Fine.

316
00:17:59,865 --> 00:18:01,401
What are you doing?

317
00:18:05,187 --> 00:18:08,071
You were supposed to give me back
my phone, but you weren't here, so...

318
00:18:08,246 --> 00:18:11,410
So you just started
going through my desk?

319
00:18:11,676 --> 00:18:14,082
I got important stuff on it.
That can't get erased.

320
00:18:15,275 --> 00:18:17,633
You just got yourself
a week's detention. Move.

321
00:18:19,757 --> 00:18:21,013
That is so unfair.

322
00:18:21,278 --> 00:18:23,952
I wouldn't have had to go through
your desk If you'd been here...

323
00:18:24,126 --> 00:18:26,280
You didn't have to do anything.

324
00:18:26,527 --> 00:18:28,351
You shouldn't have taken my phone.

325
00:18:28,615 --> 00:18:31,403
- Let's make it ten days of detention.
- What is this about?

326
00:18:31,578 --> 00:18:34,731
- Is this about your stupid contest?
- Excuse me?

327
00:18:34,997 --> 00:18:37,232
- Why are you being such an a...?
- That's it.

328
00:18:37,496 --> 00:18:40,981
I am sick of your attitude problem.
Your parents told the school to call

329
00:18:41,245 --> 00:18:43,862
- if we had any problems with you.
- Wait, what?

330
00:18:44,306 --> 00:18:47,533
And this qualifies. So we're
all going to have a little sit-down.

331
00:18:49,355 --> 00:18:51,662
- I'll take the detention.
- I'm sorry.

332
00:18:52,036 --> 00:18:53,041
It's too late.

333
00:18:53,928 --> 00:18:56,352
You don't understand.
My stepdad is a jerk.

334
00:18:56,528 --> 00:18:58,380
Everybody's a jerk.
Your stepdad, me.

335
00:18:58,646 --> 00:19:01,342
I got a thought for you.
Maybe we're not the problem.

336
00:19:01,515 --> 00:19:02,722
Maybe it's you.

337
00:19:12,547 --> 00:19:14,480
Hey, you.
What's going on?

338
00:19:14,748 --> 00:19:17,540
What does it look like?
I'm studying to get into CU.

339
00:19:17,906 --> 00:19:19,061
That's awesome.

340
00:19:19,238 --> 00:19:20,282
Little known fact,

341
00:19:20,407 --> 00:19:22,730
huge corollary between studying
and raising your grades.

342
00:19:22,868 --> 00:19:24,400
Who said anything about grades?

343
00:19:25,788 --> 00:19:28,023
I did a little research
on the Dean of Admissions.

344
00:19:28,198 --> 00:19:30,851
Her son goes to CU.
He's an S.A.T. tutor.

345
00:19:31,027 --> 00:19:32,530
- So I hired him.
- Cool.

346
00:19:32,707 --> 00:19:34,460
You're going to focus on the SATs?

347
00:19:34,676 --> 00:19:37,692
I'm gonna date the Dean's son.
Honestly, Silver, try to keep up.

348
00:19:38,836 --> 00:19:40,381
Once we start dating,

349
00:19:40,748 --> 00:19:44,123
Well, he'll take me home to Mom...
naturally I'll charm her instantly.

350
00:19:44,518 --> 00:19:47,101
Eventually, dear Richard and I
will part amicably,

351
00:19:47,236 --> 00:19:50,313
but not before the Dean and I
have forged a lasting bond.

352
00:19:50,538 --> 00:19:54,493
The type of bond that will guarantee me
a place at CU in the fall of 2011.

353
00:19:55,847 --> 00:19:59,610
Don't you think it's just a little bit
easier to... I don't know... study?

354
00:19:59,787 --> 00:20:01,851
The key to success is knowing
one's strengths.

355
00:20:01,975 --> 00:20:05,122
I am terrible at tests.
But I'm an excellent dater.

356
00:20:05,996 --> 00:20:08,911
Unfortunately, Richard
is a bit of a snooze-fest.

357
00:20:09,037 --> 00:20:11,121
His Facebook says he's some
super environmentalist.

358
00:20:11,298 --> 00:20:13,352
So I have to read
all these global warming books

359
00:20:13,488 --> 00:20:15,452
to make him think
we have stuff in common.

360
00:20:15,848 --> 00:20:18,590
Easy on the pours.
Seriously, we're in a drought here.

361
00:20:21,407 --> 00:20:24,632
What do you think? Sounds like
I care about the environment, right?

362
00:20:36,057 --> 00:20:38,292
Please, listen, just hear me out.

363
00:20:38,705 --> 00:20:40,861
All right, and afterwards
if you want me to get lost,

364
00:20:41,487 --> 00:20:43,440
I'll get lost. Forever.

365
00:20:50,767 --> 00:20:52,453
I bought you a pizza.

366
00:20:53,205 --> 00:20:56,473
'Cause when we met at the pizza parlor
we didn't know each other's ages.

367
00:20:57,548 --> 00:20:59,760
All we knew
was that we liked each other.

368
00:21:00,138 --> 00:21:02,372
And yes, when I found out
that you were older,

369
00:21:03,036 --> 00:21:03,872
I lied.

370
00:21:04,606 --> 00:21:07,622
Which was a really,
really stupid thing to do.

371
00:21:09,188 --> 00:21:10,831
The only reason why I lied,

372
00:21:11,105 --> 00:21:13,381
was because I couldn't believe

373
00:21:14,185 --> 00:21:17,360
that a girl as cool,
as down-to-earth...

374
00:21:19,105 --> 00:21:20,870
and as beautiful as you existed.

375
00:21:21,968 --> 00:21:23,442
But you want to know something?

376
00:21:23,616 --> 00:21:25,641
Although I feel terrible
about lying,

377
00:21:26,447 --> 00:21:28,240
I'm actually glad I did.

378
00:21:28,857 --> 00:21:31,210
Because if I would have
told you I was 17,

379
00:21:31,518 --> 00:21:33,160
you would have never
gone out with me.

380
00:21:33,988 --> 00:21:35,911
So yes, I lied about my age,

381
00:21:36,328 --> 00:21:38,430
but all the things
that we talked about,

382
00:21:38,728 --> 00:21:39,670
everything,

383
00:21:40,415 --> 00:21:42,243
all the stuff about
how I was feeling,

384
00:21:42,915 --> 00:21:44,213
how you were feeling,

385
00:21:44,675 --> 00:21:46,050
none of that was a lie.

386
00:21:46,228 --> 00:21:47,802
So I'm here because

387
00:21:48,305 --> 00:21:50,351
I'm hoping maybe we can start over.

388
00:21:52,985 --> 00:21:54,132
No more lies.

389
00:21:55,336 --> 00:21:57,000
Just you and me...

390
00:21:59,307 --> 00:22:01,233
and half sausage, half pepperoni.

391
00:22:02,828 --> 00:22:03,773
Get lost.

392
00:22:24,788 --> 00:22:27,551
"Please come to the meeting tonight.
I'm speaking.

393
00:22:27,838 --> 00:22:29,802
I really want to
make things right with us.

394
00:22:30,455 --> 00:22:31,501
Love, Mom."

395
00:22:34,545 --> 00:22:35,823
Right on the dashboard?

396
00:22:39,085 --> 00:22:40,823
So, are you gonna go?

397
00:22:43,415 --> 00:22:44,692
I have no idea.

398
00:22:47,288 --> 00:22:48,602
You haven't seen Metropolis?

399
00:22:48,867 --> 00:22:50,390
That's even more egregious

400
00:22:50,538 --> 00:22:52,620
than your lack of experience
with Dim Sum.

401
00:22:53,116 --> 00:22:55,043
Don't I get credit
for trying chicken feet?

402
00:22:55,166 --> 00:22:57,153
I popped back, like,
three of those suckers.

403
00:22:57,276 --> 00:22:58,813
You're right. Credit gained.

404
00:22:59,317 --> 00:23:00,622
And then it's deducted

405
00:23:01,536 --> 00:23:03,550
for your staggering
cinematic naivete.

406
00:23:03,678 --> 00:23:07,673
And no, Annie, I'm sorry,
but Kansas, it's not an excuse.

407
00:23:07,806 --> 00:23:09,511
You've lived in L.A.
for, like, a year.

408
00:23:09,637 --> 00:23:12,270
I guess I've been hanging out
in the wrong scene.

409
00:23:12,407 --> 00:23:13,760
Yeah, no kidding.

410
00:23:14,207 --> 00:23:17,173
It's gonna blow your mind, Metropolis.
It's huge. It's all about

411
00:23:17,298 --> 00:23:18,940
man versus society.

412
00:23:19,066 --> 00:23:20,693
Big influence
on the movie I'm making.

413
00:23:21,428 --> 00:23:23,013
You're making a movie?

414
00:23:23,388 --> 00:23:25,513
Half narrative, half documentary,

415
00:23:25,716 --> 00:23:28,770
half really just sick
experimental stuff.

416
00:23:28,907 --> 00:23:31,943
Think like, Matthew Barney
meets, Michael Moore.

417
00:23:32,255 --> 00:23:33,050
Cool.

418
00:23:34,497 --> 00:23:35,841
Actually there's,

419
00:23:36,807 --> 00:23:39,443
there's a band playing tonight,
The Script.

420
00:23:39,565 --> 00:23:41,922
Thought I might use them
for part of my score. Do you...

421
00:23:42,478 --> 00:23:43,501
want to come?

422
00:23:44,037 --> 00:23:45,922
- Where are they playing?
- The Beach Club.

423
00:23:47,327 --> 00:23:50,761
I will pass. Most of the people
I hate hang out there, so...

424
00:23:51,858 --> 00:23:54,310
What if I guaranteed you wouldn't
have to see any of them?

425
00:23:55,105 --> 00:23:56,223
Then would you go?

426
00:24:26,287 --> 00:24:28,841
- Are you Richard?
- Naomi, hi.

427
00:24:29,245 --> 00:24:31,092
Oh, I'm so sorry I'm late.

428
00:24:31,307 --> 00:24:34,172
They really should repaint
the bike lanes by the Shrine.

429
00:24:37,086 --> 00:24:38,843
You rode your bike here
from Beverly Hills?

430
00:24:38,977 --> 00:24:41,640
Just doing what I can to
reduce my carbon footprint.

431
00:24:43,778 --> 00:24:44,902
That's impressive.

432
00:24:45,386 --> 00:24:46,403
No, stop.

433
00:24:46,568 --> 00:24:48,690
No, seriously, I feel
like I'm surrounded by people

434
00:24:48,867 --> 00:24:50,882
who don't care about
the Earth. They just

435
00:24:51,126 --> 00:24:52,870
guzzle water
from plastic water bottles...

436
00:24:53,005 --> 00:24:54,990
How do they sleep at night?

437
00:24:55,167 --> 00:24:57,571
No idea.
You know what, I wish

438
00:24:57,705 --> 00:25:00,101
we could put pictures
of choking dolphins on the bottles.

439
00:25:00,367 --> 00:25:02,902
I think maybe then they'd think
twice about using them.

440
00:25:03,398 --> 00:25:05,003
Choking dolphins would be awesome.

441
00:25:08,666 --> 00:25:10,802
Before we get started with vocab,
do you know

442
00:25:10,967 --> 00:25:13,132
where the Independent Theater
is around here?

443
00:25:13,265 --> 00:25:14,912
I heard there's a showing of <i>FLOW,</i>

444
00:25:15,047 --> 00:25:17,523
and I just wanted to see
if I could catch it later tonight.

445
00:25:17,645 --> 00:25:19,050
<i>FLOW</i> as in <i>For Love Of Water?</i>

446
00:25:21,596 --> 00:25:24,412
I tried catching the re-release
last night, but they were sold out.

447
00:25:24,857 --> 00:25:27,960
Rumor has it that you'll never
view water politics the same way again.

448
00:25:28,086 --> 00:25:29,581
Well, hey, you should come.

449
00:25:30,007 --> 00:25:32,001
I mean, I have another ticket.

450
00:25:35,228 --> 00:25:37,800
You know, I'm your tutor.
I'm not sure that's appropriate.

451
00:25:39,078 --> 00:25:40,420
Come on, it's not a date.

452
00:25:40,557 --> 00:25:43,502
It's just two like-minded
individuals going to see a film

453
00:25:43,627 --> 00:25:45,602
about something they're
passionate about.

454
00:25:45,738 --> 00:25:47,711
Plus, I hear it's
kind of one of those flicks

455
00:25:47,846 --> 00:25:50,573
you've got to see on the big screen.
Kind of like <i>The Dark Knight.</i>

456
00:25:53,097 --> 00:25:54,791
God, you're tempting me.

457
00:25:56,238 --> 00:25:58,840
Yeah, you know, what the hell.
It's just one movie.

458
00:25:59,847 --> 00:26:00,641
Great.

459
00:26:01,437 --> 00:26:02,232
Vocab.

460
00:26:12,117 --> 00:26:13,871
- Sorry we're late.
- Hey, no worries.

461
00:26:14,135 --> 00:26:16,301
- How are you, buddy?
- Good, man, how you doing?

462
00:26:16,986 --> 00:26:18,133
What, no hug?

463
00:26:18,847 --> 00:26:19,953
Oh, of course.

464
00:26:21,338 --> 00:26:22,731
Guys, this is Jasmine.

465
00:26:22,857 --> 00:26:24,172
Jasmine, this is...

466
00:26:24,356 --> 00:26:25,750
Hey, I'm Adrianna.

467
00:26:25,875 --> 00:26:26,870
And Navid.

468
00:26:27,395 --> 00:26:28,283
Have a seat.

469
00:26:36,096 --> 00:26:38,661
Jazz... just moved to L.A.
from Kauai.

470
00:26:38,876 --> 00:26:40,571
No kidding. Sweet.

471
00:26:40,705 --> 00:26:42,723
Ade, you went there once, right?
With your mom?

472
00:26:42,985 --> 00:26:45,641
- Yeah, a long time ago.
- Yeah, I remember.

473
00:26:46,518 --> 00:26:49,321
When she came back,
she would not take off her lei.

474
00:26:49,456 --> 00:26:51,520
I'm telling you,
this thing was not only wilting,

475
00:26:51,695 --> 00:26:53,311
but it was actually
starting to stink.

476
00:26:54,617 --> 00:26:57,242
You know, my family actually vacations
In Kauai every Christmas.

477
00:26:57,656 --> 00:26:58,873
Right on. Whereabouts?

478
00:26:59,007 --> 00:27:01,252
North Shore. It's like,
one of the most beautiful...

479
00:27:01,377 --> 00:27:03,280
I'm starving!
Should we look at the menu?

480
00:27:03,455 --> 00:27:04,250
Sure.

481
00:27:07,505 --> 00:27:09,911
Hey, honey, do you want
to order two dishes and split?

482
00:27:10,308 --> 00:27:11,711
Yeah, sounds good.

483
00:27:12,546 --> 00:27:14,300
Can I get you guys
something to drink?

484
00:27:14,785 --> 00:27:17,983
I think I'll have an iced tea.
No, make that an Arnold Palmer.

485
00:27:18,817 --> 00:27:20,310
I'm good with water.

486
00:27:20,757 --> 00:27:22,540
I think we're all good for water.

487
00:27:23,157 --> 00:27:24,252
Okay, great.

488
00:27:25,098 --> 00:27:26,993
- Oh, babe.
- Oh, my God...

489
00:27:27,275 --> 00:27:29,100
I got it. Don't worry about it.

490
00:27:34,598 --> 00:27:36,611
I am very impressed, Liam.

491
00:27:37,057 --> 00:27:39,921
It only took a month for us
to get called into school.

492
00:27:40,505 --> 00:27:43,270
You held it together a whole lot longer
than I thought you would.

493
00:27:43,397 --> 00:27:45,241
Sweetheart, I know
this is tough for you

494
00:27:45,416 --> 00:27:46,600
but we had an agreement.

495
00:27:46,725 --> 00:27:48,643
- If he screwed up one more time...
- I know,

496
00:27:48,776 --> 00:27:50,271
Sweetheart, we gave him a shot.

497
00:27:51,018 --> 00:27:53,220
We let him move back
into the house, but obviously

498
00:27:53,356 --> 00:27:54,412
it's not working.

499
00:27:55,058 --> 00:27:57,182
Some kids are just
bad seeds, you know?

500
00:27:57,306 --> 00:27:58,440
Liam is one of those.

