00:28:04,528 --> 00:28:07,052
Jeffrey Sarkossian.
This is my wife, Colleen.

502
00:28:08,255 --> 00:28:09,772
Ryan Matthews. Nice to meet you.

503
00:28:09,958 --> 00:28:11,850
Look, I wanted to apologize

504
00:28:12,028 --> 00:28:14,583
ahead of time for whatever
trouble Liam got himself into.

505
00:28:15,015 --> 00:28:15,912
Trouble?

506
00:28:17,525 --> 00:28:19,063
Liam hasn't gotten into any trouble.

507
00:28:20,075 --> 00:28:23,241
Listen, the reason I called you both
down here was to tell you in person

508
00:28:24,445 --> 00:28:26,172
how great Liam's been doing.

509
00:28:27,088 --> 00:28:29,420
His first paper was terrific.

510
00:28:30,075 --> 00:28:33,121
It was insightful, well structured,
beautifully written.

511
00:28:33,636 --> 00:28:34,711
Oh, honey.

512
00:28:35,258 --> 00:28:36,670
You should be very proud of him.

513
00:28:53,598 --> 00:28:55,642
Okay, everyone, welcome.

514
00:28:55,775 --> 00:28:57,813
My name is Tim,
and I'm an alcoholic.

515
00:28:58,158 --> 00:28:59,552
Hi, Tim.

516
00:29:02,838 --> 00:29:04,132
Sorry, I'm late.

517
00:29:07,325 --> 00:29:08,270
So...

518
00:29:09,815 --> 00:29:11,082
what you did...

519
00:29:11,865 --> 00:29:12,942
that was cool.

520
00:29:14,706 --> 00:29:17,003
The ten days of detention
still stand.

521
00:29:18,255 --> 00:29:19,210
Yeah, okay.

522
00:29:23,007 --> 00:29:23,960
Your phone.

523
00:29:27,456 --> 00:29:28,302
Thanks.

524
00:29:33,558 --> 00:29:35,182
That essay contest thing.

525
00:29:37,428 --> 00:29:38,852
Did I miss the deadline?

526
00:29:40,427 --> 00:29:41,220
Nope.

527
00:29:41,878 --> 00:29:43,172
Three days left.

528
00:29:45,107 --> 00:29:46,012
Cool.

529
00:29:54,078 --> 00:29:55,372
So I hiked the waterfall.

530
00:29:55,506 --> 00:29:58,270
Of course, I thought it was
three miles instead of nine.

531
00:29:58,408 --> 00:30:01,002
And I ran out of water, and...
I vomited.

532
00:30:03,855 --> 00:30:06,593
I gotta go to the ladies' room.
I'll be right back.

533
00:30:06,768 --> 00:30:08,111
Okay, sure, babe.

534
00:30:09,566 --> 00:30:12,162
Do you want to try
any French onion soup?

535
00:30:24,736 --> 00:30:27,503
- What's wrong with you?
- What are you talking about?

536
00:30:27,625 --> 00:30:29,770
You know exactly
what I'm talking about.

537
00:30:29,905 --> 00:30:32,440
Why would you ask Navid and I
on a double date?

538
00:30:32,565 --> 00:30:34,312
Just thought it'd be fun.

539
00:30:34,806 --> 00:30:35,902
Yeah, right.

540
00:30:36,208 --> 00:30:39,270
And you had to make out with Jasmine
right in front of me. Really?

541
00:30:39,406 --> 00:30:42,383
I'm sorry. Did that bother you?
It's interesting because

542
00:30:42,545 --> 00:30:44,303
- you know what bothered me?
- What?

543
00:30:44,467 --> 00:30:46,860
Having to listen to Navid
brag about having sex with you

544
00:30:46,988 --> 00:30:48,512
right after we kissed.

545
00:30:48,638 --> 00:30:50,742
So this is about getting revenge?

546
00:30:51,328 --> 00:30:54,601
What do you care who I make out with?
You've got a boyfriend, remember?

547
00:30:54,775 --> 00:30:57,313
I know I have a boyfriend.
I don't need you to remind me.

548
00:30:57,487 --> 00:30:58,952
So why are you acting so jealous?

549
00:30:59,085 --> 00:31:01,480
I'm not acting jealous!
It's just really annoying

550
00:31:01,657 --> 00:31:04,303
because I know that
you're trying to make me jealous.

551
00:31:05,035 --> 00:31:06,333
So what if I am?

552
00:31:07,046 --> 00:31:10,592
- It's obviously working.
- It's not working. It's pathetic.

553
00:31:11,626 --> 00:31:14,472
Okay, you know what?
I really could care less.

554
00:31:15,477 --> 00:31:17,503
- Kiss whoever you want.
- Okay fine.

555
00:31:17,837 --> 00:31:18,630
Fine.

556
00:31:27,958 --> 00:31:29,902
You shouldn't have done that.

557
00:31:40,776 --> 00:31:43,020
I'm sorry you're not feeling good.

558
00:31:43,355 --> 00:31:46,950
- You still want me to come over?
- No, I just need to sleep.

559
00:31:49,255 --> 00:31:50,903
Sure everything's okay?

560
00:31:51,206 --> 00:31:52,603
Everything's fine.

561
00:31:52,895 --> 00:31:55,242
Am I not allowed to have a headache?

562
00:31:55,456 --> 00:31:57,103
Yeah, of course. Sorry.

563
00:32:10,756 --> 00:32:12,550
You look like you're lost.

564
00:32:16,365 --> 00:32:18,213
I'm looking for Reed Tower.

565
00:32:18,935 --> 00:32:20,680
I'm going that way. Come on.

566
00:32:21,846 --> 00:32:22,842
Thank you.

567
00:32:22,977 --> 00:32:24,571
I'm Jamie, by the way.

568
00:32:25,527 --> 00:32:27,322
I take it you don't go here?

569
00:32:27,455 --> 00:32:29,121
No, I'm going to apply.

570
00:32:29,258 --> 00:32:31,071
Yeah, you should, it's the best.

571
00:32:31,338 --> 00:32:34,071
And you, you are a Pi Phi
waiting to happen.

572
00:32:35,765 --> 00:32:37,373
So, you're psychic?

573
00:32:37,627 --> 00:32:40,291
Psychic, SAE pledge...
same thing.

574
00:32:40,877 --> 00:32:42,570
Yeah, we... know things.

575
00:32:43,526 --> 00:32:44,521
Like what?

576
00:32:45,187 --> 00:32:46,031
Like...

577
00:32:46,996 --> 00:32:49,591
I know when I see someone
I have to meet.

578
00:32:50,037 --> 00:32:53,173
Why do you think I threw
my football at you yesterday?

579
00:32:53,478 --> 00:32:55,332
What, you thought
that was an accident?

580
00:32:55,458 --> 00:32:57,072
No, my arm is pretty damn accurate.

581
00:32:57,206 --> 00:33:00,850
Don't think I would've made it
on the football team otherwise.

582
00:33:00,978 --> 00:33:02,620
So, you're on the team.

583
00:33:04,956 --> 00:33:07,602
Would you want to come
to a game sometime?

584
00:33:07,747 --> 00:33:10,343
There you are.
I was afraid you got lost.

585
00:33:13,257 --> 00:33:15,901
I was actually just
asking for directions.

586
00:33:16,176 --> 00:33:18,320
- Jamie, this is...
- My roommate Richard.

587
00:33:25,138 --> 00:33:28,281
So, we should get going
if we want to catch the bus.

588
00:33:37,568 --> 00:33:40,011
So, these guys are from Ireland?
Cool.

589
00:33:43,046 --> 00:33:44,833
I'm sorry, man.
Just...

590
00:33:44,965 --> 00:33:49,010
not really in the best mood. Hoping
that music gets my mind off Sasha.

591
00:33:49,588 --> 00:33:50,560
No problem.

592
00:33:50,738 --> 00:33:53,482
- So, what do you want to drink?
- Whatever.

593
00:33:55,327 --> 00:33:58,322
- What are you doing here?
- Look, I just came for the music.

594
00:33:58,448 --> 00:34:00,121
I had no idea
you were going to be here.

595
00:34:00,246 --> 00:34:02,182
The musicians are friends of mine.

596
00:34:02,636 --> 00:34:03,833
Adult friends.

597
00:34:04,778 --> 00:34:05,772
I'm sorry.

598
00:34:07,365 --> 00:34:08,312
Let's go.

599
00:34:13,627 --> 00:34:15,023
You want to split?

600
00:34:15,286 --> 00:34:18,580
So, thanks, everyone, for coming down.
We're The Script from Dublin,

601
00:34:18,707 --> 00:34:21,753
and the song we're going to do
is called "We Cry."

602
00:34:22,297 --> 00:34:24,171
Let's just stay for the set,
you know?

603
00:34:24,295 --> 00:34:26,392
- Then we'll bounce.
- All right.

604
00:35:02,438 --> 00:35:04,533
Told you we could hear the music

605
00:35:04,658 --> 00:35:07,651
- without seeing anyone you hate.
- It's perfect.

606
00:35:11,337 --> 00:35:12,131
What?

607
00:35:14,108 --> 00:35:16,140
Nothing. Nothing. Just...

608
00:35:17,975 --> 00:35:19,420
Thank you for this.

609
00:35:34,887 --> 00:35:38,263
And I have let down...
so many people over the years

610
00:35:38,385 --> 00:35:39,682
I've lost count.

611
00:35:40,797 --> 00:35:43,492
But the ones that I regret
hurting the most

612
00:35:44,458 --> 00:35:45,750
are my children.

613
00:35:50,157 --> 00:35:52,101
I was such a terrible mother.

614
00:35:53,415 --> 00:35:55,653
Which is why I'm so grateful that...

615
00:35:56,165 --> 00:35:58,462
one of my daughters is here tonight.

616
00:35:59,855 --> 00:36:01,201
Thank you, honey,

617
00:36:01,465 --> 00:36:03,411
for giving me another chance.

618
00:36:05,028 --> 00:36:08,490
I promise you,
I will not let you down again.

619
00:36:14,628 --> 00:36:16,381
I'd like to say
something, if I could.

620
00:36:16,518 --> 00:36:17,861
Go ahead. Please.

621
00:36:27,016 --> 00:36:30,681
I really wanted to be here tonight
so that I could tell my mother,

622
00:36:31,367 --> 00:36:32,712
once and for all,

623
00:36:33,675 --> 00:36:35,223
to stay away from me.

624
00:36:36,277 --> 00:36:37,813
Everything that she said?

625
00:36:37,948 --> 00:36:41,042
Trust me, it's going to last
until she's a bad day.

626
00:36:41,826 --> 00:36:44,110
Then she's going
to go back to the bottle or,

627
00:36:44,246 --> 00:36:47,043
the pills, whatever
she can get her hands on.

628
00:36:49,487 --> 00:36:52,032
But you did get
one thing right, Jackie.

629
00:36:53,858 --> 00:36:55,700
You were a terrible mother.

630
00:36:56,676 --> 00:37:01,171
The worst of the worst. And if you think
that you can buy me back with a car...

631
00:37:02,408 --> 00:37:04,840
That's just proof
that you don't know me at all.

632
00:37:07,795 --> 00:37:09,791
Stay away from me.
I mean it.

633
00:37:11,176 --> 00:37:12,472
You're dead to me.

634
00:37:34,976 --> 00:37:36,492
Let's just go, man.

635
00:37:36,938 --> 00:37:39,481
It's hard being
in the same room as her.

636
00:37:40,186 --> 00:37:41,481
Yeah, it's cool.

637
00:37:45,395 --> 00:37:46,263
Actually...

638
00:37:46,848 --> 00:37:48,830
- give me ten minutes.
- When did she get here?

639
00:37:48,966 --> 00:37:52,260
I don't know. But I got to act
while I got an opening.

640
00:37:52,746 --> 00:37:54,342
Go do your thing, man.

641
00:38:17,786 --> 00:38:20,582
- You already talked to her?
- There's nothing to talk about anymore.

642
00:38:20,716 --> 00:38:22,703
I'm too late. She moved on.

643
00:38:23,756 --> 00:38:25,603
Let's just get out of here.

644
00:38:31,767 --> 00:38:33,262
Where are you going?

645
00:38:37,497 --> 00:38:40,091
That kiss wasn't appropriate
for a tutor.

646
00:38:40,448 --> 00:38:43,513
I'm sorry. I know this is not
supposed to be a date.

647
00:38:43,647 --> 00:38:45,822
I'm just having such a good time.

648
00:38:47,478 --> 00:38:48,373
Me, too.

649
00:38:49,697 --> 00:38:52,140
I got to say,
you really surprised me.

650
00:38:52,346 --> 00:38:54,550
When I first heard "Beverly Hills,"
I thought, "Great.

651
00:38:54,678 --> 00:38:57,970
She's going to be about
clothes, and hair, and makeup."

652
00:38:59,446 --> 00:39:00,790
Man, was I wrong.

653
00:39:01,418 --> 00:39:02,362
You're...

654
00:39:03,346 --> 00:39:05,041
pretty unique, you know?

655
00:39:05,908 --> 00:39:06,852
You, too.

656
00:39:07,478 --> 00:39:09,970
You must have pretty
inspiring parents.

657
00:39:10,558 --> 00:39:12,603
What are they like, by the way?

658
00:39:12,726 --> 00:39:13,770
My parents?

659
00:39:15,198 --> 00:39:17,570
Pretty normal.
My... dad's a radiologist.

660
00:39:17,707 --> 00:39:20,802
And my mom's actually
the Dean of Admissions at CU.

661
00:39:21,376 --> 00:39:22,220
Really?

662
00:39:22,625 --> 00:39:23,731
I had no idea.

663
00:39:33,448 --> 00:39:36,390
<i>Naomi will never believe
that we slept together.</i>

664
00:40:03,785 --> 00:40:04,833
I really...

665
00:40:05,707 --> 00:40:07,203
need to talk to you.

666
00:40:08,598 --> 00:40:10,793
And I'm sorry for the way I acted.

667
00:40:12,778 --> 00:40:14,222
Call me back, okay?

668
00:40:24,615 --> 00:40:25,410
Hello?

669
00:40:28,778 --> 00:40:30,661
This is the last time, okay?

670
00:40:31,968 --> 00:40:33,813
We're just saying good-bye.

671
00:40:40,426 --> 00:40:41,821
Ade, are you okay?

672
00:40:45,217 --> 00:40:46,811
Is it the Teddy thing?

673
00:40:47,105 --> 00:40:48,900
It didn't go away, did it?

674
00:40:49,447 --> 00:40:51,891
I mean yes, you were right,
it didn't.

675
00:40:52,957 --> 00:40:54,650
That's not why I'm here.

676
00:40:57,088 --> 00:41:00,861
Silver, we're friends. Okay?
We have to stay in each other's lives.

677
00:41:00,996 --> 00:41:02,831
I know. I'm sorry that we fought.

678
00:41:03,006 --> 00:41:04,451
Your mom called me.

679
00:41:05,657 --> 00:41:07,003
Ade, let it go.

680
00:41:07,286 --> 00:41:09,511
She just wanted advice
on how to get through to you.

681
00:41:09,645 --> 00:41:11,082
She shouldn't have bothered you.

682
00:41:11,215 --> 00:41:12,960
No, you don't understand.

683
00:41:13,978 --> 00:41:16,300
She told me something
you don't know.

684
00:41:17,267 --> 00:41:20,510
Please. There's nothing that
that woman could tell you

685
00:41:20,636 --> 00:41:22,513
that will make me change my mind.

686
00:41:22,647 --> 00:41:24,390
Our relationship is over.

687
00:41:26,576 --> 00:41:27,983
She has cancer, Silver.

688
00:41:32,625 --> 00:41:34,021
Your mom is dying.

